\layout Abstract

This chapter presents an incomplete review of the Gauss-Kuzmin-Wirsing (GKW)
 operator.
 The GKW operator is the transfer operator of the Gauss map, and thus has
 connections to the theory of continued fractions.
\layout Abstract

The operator appears to be quite complex itself, and difficult to solve.
 Eigenfunctions can be obtained numerically, but little else is known in
 the mathematical literature.
 
